### 7. COPY MODEL IMPLEMENTATION (Business Logic)

**File:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489911601-q4vnve/server/images.go` (lines 397-434)

```go
func CopyModel(src, dst model.Name) error {
	// Validate both names are fully qualified
	if !dst.IsFullyQualified() {
		return model.Unqualified(dst)
	}
	if !src.IsFullyQualified() {
		return model.Unqualified(src)
	}

	// If source and destination are the same, no-op
	if src.Filepath() == dst.Filepath() {
		return nil
	}

	// Get manifest directory
	manifests, err := manifest.Path()
	if err != nil {
		return err
	}

	// Create destination directory if needed
	dstpath := filepath.Join(manifests, dst.Filepath())
	if err := os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(dstpath), 0o755); err != nil {
		return err
	}

	// Copy manifest file from source to destination
	srcpath := filepath.Join(manifests, src.Filepath())
	srcfile, err := os.Open(srcpath)
	if err != nil {
		return err
	}
	defer srcfile.Close()

	dstfile, err := os.Create(dstpath)
	if err != nil {
		return err
	}
	defer dstfile.Close()

	_, err = io.Copy(dstfile, srcfile)
	return err
}
```

**Key insight for rename:** Copy only copies the manifest file, not the blob layers. Layers are shared between models and managed via reference counting in `RemoveLayers()`.

