### 12. MODEL NAME STRUCTURE

**File:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489911601-q4vnve/types/model/name.go` (lines 88-303)

Models have a hierarchical naming structure:

```go
type Name struct {
	Host           string  // Registry host (e.g., "registry.ollama.ai")
	Namespace      string  // Namespace (e.g., "library")
	Model          string  // Model name (e.g., "llama2")
	Tag            string  // Tag/version (e.g., "latest" or "13b")
	ProtocolScheme string  // "https"
}

// String representation: "host/namespace/model:tag"
// Default values:
//   Host: "registry.ollama.ai"
//   Namespace: "library"
//   Tag: "latest"

// Filepath returns: "host/namespace/model/tag" for manifest storage
func (n Name) Filepath() string {
	return filepath.Join(n.Host, n.Namespace, n.Model, n.Tag)
}
```

